CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 27, 1954, pg. 13 reads: "The Glamorous Cotillion - Scenes from the third annual debutante Cotillion given by Pittsburgh AKAs include...center, the glamorous debutantes of 1954 pose for the photographer..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of fourteen young women, including Luella Blow, seated fourth from left, wearing light colored evening gowns and gloves, holding bouquets, gathered in Syria Mosque for the Alpha Kappa Alpha's 1954 Cotillion
